<h3></h3>
<div class='layout'><p>9 Microfarm</p><p>第九章 微生农场</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>MYCOGEN: …………microfarms of Mycogen……legendary, though they survive today only in such oft-used similes as "rich as……microfarms of Mycogen" or "tasty as Mycogenian yeast." Such encomiums tend to intensify with time, to be sure,……Hari Seldon visited those microfarms in……course of……Flight……there……references in……memoirs that would tend to support……popular opinion……</p><p>麦曲生：……麦曲生的微生农场颇具传奇色彩，不过如今却仅保存于一些譬喻中，诸如“如同麦曲生微生农场那般丰饶”“有如麦曲生酵母那般美味”。事实上，这种赞美有与日俱增之势。但“逃亡期”的哈里·谢顿曾造访过那些微生农场，而他在回忆录中所记载的见闻，则倾向于支持这个公认的看法……</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>ENCYCLOPEDIA GALACTICA</p><p>……《银河百科全书》</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"That……good." said Seldon explosively.……was considerably better than……food Graycloud brought--"</p><p>“真好吃！”谢顿爆出一声赞叹，“比灰云带来的食物好得多……”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors said reasonably, "You have to remember that Grayclouds woman……to prepare it on short notice in……middle of……night."……paused……said, "I wish they would……wife. They make woman sound like such an appanage, like my house or my robe. It is absolutely demeaning."</p><p>铎丝以中肯的态度说：“你别忘了，灰云的女人得在半夜临时准备。”她顿了顿，又说，“我真希望他们会说‘妻子’。他们让‘女人’听来只像一种附属品，就像‘我的房子’或‘我的袍子’一样。这绝对是贬抑的称呼。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I know.……infuriating.……they might well make wife sound like an appanage as well.……the……they live……the Sisters don't seem to mind.……and I aren't going to change it by lecturing. Anyway,……you……how……Sisters……it?"</p><p>“我知道，这的确令人气愤。但他们大可让‘妻子’听来也像一种附属品。这是他们的生活方式，姐妹们似乎并不在意。你我不必劝喻他们做任何改变……不管这些，你看到两位姐妹如何烹饪了吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Yes, I……and they made everything seem very simple. I doubted I could remember everything they did,……they insisted I wouldnt have……I could……away with mere heating. I gathered……bread……some sort of microderivative added to it in……baking that both raised……dough……lent it that crunchy consistency……warm flavor. Just a hint of pepper, didnt……think?"</p><p>“看到了，她们让每件事看来都非常简单。我怀疑自己能否记得她们所做的一切，可是她们坚持没有这个必要，我只要会加热便能应付。我推测那些面包在烘焙过程中，曾经加入某种微生衍生物，不但让面团胀了起来，还让它带有爽脆的硬度和亲切的香味。只有一点点辛辣，你不觉得吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I couldnt tell,……whatever it was, I didnt……enough.……the soup.……you recognize……of……vegetables?"</p><p>“我无法判断，但不论加了什么，我都没吃够。还有这碗汤，你认得出里面的蔬菜吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"No."</p><p>“认不出来。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"And what……the sliced meat? Could……tell?"</p><p>“这些肉片又是什么？你能分辨吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I don't think it……sliced meat, actually. We……have a lamb dish back on Cinna that it reminded me of."</p><p>“其实，我认为它并不是肉片，虽然它的确令我想起锡纳的羔羊肉。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"It……certainly……lamb."</p><p>“绝不是羔羊肉。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I said that I doubted it……meat aaaall.--I don't think anyone outside Mycogen eats like this either.……even……Emperor, Im sure. Whatever……Mycogenians sell……Im willing to bet, near……bottom of……line. They save……best……themselves. We……better……stay here……long, Hari. If we……used to eating like this, well never be able to acclimatize ourselves to……miserable stuff they have outside."……laughed.</p><p>“我说过，我怀疑它根本不是肉类……我认为麦曲生以外的人都没吃过这样的好东西。就连皇帝也没有，我敢肯定。麦曲生卖出去的那些，我愿意打赌，全部是下等货色。他们把上好的留给自己享用。哈里，我们最好别在这里待太久。假如我们习惯了这种吃法，就再也不能适应外面那些低贱的食物。”说完她哈哈大笑。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon laughed too. He took another……aaathe fruit juice, which tasted……more tantalizing than……fruit juice he……ever sipped before,……said, "listen, when Hummin took me to……University, we stopped at a roadside diner……had some food that……heavily yeasted. It tasted like--……never mind what it tasted like,……I wouldnt have thought it conceivable, then, that microfood could taste like this. I wish……Sisters were still here. It would have been polite to thank them."</p><p>谢顿也笑了起来。他又呷了一口果汁，那味道远比他喝过的任何果汁都醉人得多。“听我说，当夫铭带我到大学去的时候，我们曾经停在一个路边速食店，吃了一些添加浓重酵母的食物。味道好像……不，别管味道像什么，反正，当时我绝不会相信微生食品能有这种美味。我希望两位姐妹还在这里，礼貌上应该向她们致谢。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I think they were quite aware of……we would feel. I remarked on……wonderful smell while everything……warming……they said, quite complacently, that it would taste even better."</p><p>“我想她们相当清楚我们会有什么感受。当菜肴还在加热的时候，我赞美着散发出来的绝妙香气，她们则以相当自满的口气说，其实吃起来味道会更好。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"The older……said that, I imagine."</p><p>“年纪较大的那个说的吧，我猜。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Yes.……younger……giggled.--And theyll be back. Theyre going to bring me a kirtle, so that I……go……to……the shops with them.……they made it clear I would have to wash my face if I……to be seen in public. They will show me where to……some good-quality kirtles of my……and where I……buy ready-made meals of……kinds.……I'll have to do is heaaathem……They explained that decent Sisters wouldnt do that,……would start from scratch. In fact, some of……meal they prepared……us……simply heated……they apologized……that. They managed to imply, though, that tribespeople couldnt be expected to appreciate true artistry in cooking, so that simply heating prepared food would do……us.--They seem to take it……granted, by……way, that I will be doing……the shopping……cooking."</p><p>“没错，年轻的那个只是吃吃笑。她们还会再来，会帮我带一套裰服，这样我就能跟她们出去逛街。她们讲得很明白，我若想出现在公共场所，就必须把脸上的妆洗掉。她们会告诉我哪里能买到高级的裰服，还有哪里能买到各种熟食……我需要做的只有加热而已。她们解释说，有教养的姐妹都不会那样做，一定都会从头做起。事实上，在她们为我们准备的食物中，有些也是加热一下即可，她们还特地为此道歉。不过，她们在话中透露了一项讯息，那就是无法指望外族人懂得欣赏真正的厨艺，所以只要把熟食加热就能打发我们。对了，她们似乎认为，我理所当然会负责所有采购和烹饪的工作。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"As we……at home, When in Trantor, do as……Trantorians……"</p><p>“就好像我们家乡的一句俗话：在川陀行，如川陀人。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Yes, I……sure that would be your attitude in this case."</p><p>“是啊，我早就知道你对这件事的态度会是这样。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Im only human," said Seldon.</p><p>“我只是个凡人。”谢顿说。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"The usual excuse," said Dors with a small smile. </p><p>“老套的借口。”铎丝露出浅浅的微笑。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon leaned back with a satisfactory well-fI'lled feeling……said, "Youve been on Trantor……two years, Dors, so……might understand a……things that I don't. Is it your opinion thaaathis……social system……Mycogenians have is part of a supernaturalistic view they have?"</p><p>谢顿带着一种心满意足的充实感仰靠在椅背上。“铎丝，你来川陀已经两年，所以你或许了解一些我不了解的事。在你的见解中，麦曲生这种古怪的社会系统，是不是他们的‘超自然宇宙观’的一环？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Supernaturalistic?"</p><p>“超自然？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Yes. Would……have heard that this……so?"</p><p>“对，你会不会刚好听说过？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"What do……mean by supernaturalistic?"</p><p>“你所谓的‘超自然’是什么意思？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"The obvious. A belief in entities that……independent of natural law, that……not bound by……conservation of energy,……instance, or by……existence of a constant of action."</p><p>“最明显的意思……相信某些实体独立于自然律之外，比如说不受能量守恒或作用量常数的限制。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I see. Youre asking if Mycogen is a religious community."</p><p>“我懂了，你是在问麦曲生是不是一个宗教性社会。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>It……Seldons turn. "Religious?"</p><p>这回轮到谢顿困惑不已。“宗教？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Yes.……an archaic term,……we historians……it--our study is riddled with archaic terms. Religious is……precisely equivalent to supernaturalistic, though it contains richly supernaturalistic elements. I can't answer your specific question, however, because……never made……special investigation of Mycogen. still, from what little……seen of……place……from my knowledge of religions in history, I wouldnt be surprised if……Mycogenian society……religious in character."</p><p>“是的。这是个古老的词汇，不过我们历史学家经常使用……我们的研究充满古老的词汇。‘宗教’并不完全等同于‘超自然’，但它含有丰富的超自然成分。然而，我无法回答你这个特定的问题，因为我从未对麦曲生做过任何特别研究。话说回来，根据我在此地的一点所见所闻，以及我对古老宗教的认识，倘若麦曲生社会具有宗教本质，我也不会惊讶。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"In that case, would it surprise……if Mycogenian legends were also religious in character?"</p><p>“这样的话，如果麦曲生的传说也具有宗教本质，你会不会惊讶？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"No, it wouldnt."</p><p>“不会。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"And therefore……based on historical matter?"</p><p>“因此没有历史根据？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"That wouldnt necessarily follow.……core of……legends might still be authentically historic, allowing……distortion……supernaturalistic intermixture."</p><p>“这倒不一定。传说的核心仍有可能是货真价实的历史，只不过遭到扭曲，并掺杂了超自然的成分。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Ah," said Seldon……seemed to retire into……thoughts.</p><p>“啊。”谢顿说完之后，似乎便陷入沉思。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Finally Dors broke……silence that followed……said, "Its……so uncommon,……know. There is a considerable religious element on many worlds.……grown stronger in……last……centuries as……Empire……grown more turbulent. On my world of Cinna, at least a quarter of……population is tritheistic."</p><p>最后由铎丝打破沉默，她说：“你知道吗，这没什么不寻常的。许多世界都带有可观的宗教成分，而过去这几个世纪，随着帝国越来越动荡，宗教的势力也越来越强。在我自己的世界锡纳，至少有四分之一人口是三神论的信徒。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon……again painfully……regretfully conscious of……ignorance of history. He said, "Were there times in past history when religion……more prominent than it is today?"</p><p>谢顿再度察觉自己对历史的无知，因而深感痛苦与懊悔。他说：“历史上，有比如今更盛行宗教的时期吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Certainly. In addition, there……new varieties springing up constantly.……Mycogenian religion, whatever it might……could be relatively……and……be restricted to Mycogen itself. I couldnt really tell without considerable study."</p><p>“当然有。除此之外，还不断有新生的派别冒出来。不论麦曲生拥有什么宗教，都有可能相当新颖，也或许仅局限于麦曲生一区。尚未进行深入研究之前，我不能下任何断言。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"But……we……to……point of……Dors. Is it your opinion that women……more……to be religious than……are?"</p><p>“铎丝，可是现在我们谈到重点了。在你的见解中，女性是否比男性更具宗教倾向？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors Venabili raised……eyebrows.……not sure if we……assume anything as simple as that."……thought a bit. "I suspect that those elements of a population that have a smaller stake in……material natural world……more……to find solace in what……call supernaturalism--the poor,……disinherited,……downtrodden. Insofar as supernaturalism overlaps religion, they……also be more religious. There……obviously many exceptions in both directions. Many of……downtrodden……lack religion; many of……rich, powerful,……satisfied……possess it."</p><p>铎丝·凡纳比里扬起双眉。“我不确定我们能否做这么简单的假设。”她稍微想了一下，“根据我的猜想，在物质世界中拥有较少本钱的成员，比较容易在你所谓的超自然论中找到慰藉，例如穷人、家世欠佳者，以及遭受压迫的人。在超自然论和宗教的交集部分，他们可能也会比较虔诚。但是两方面显然都有不少例外，许多受压迫者可能缺乏宗教信仰，许多有钱有势、生活安逸的人反而信教。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"But in Mycogen," said Seldon, "where……women seem to be treated as subhuman--would I be right in assuming they would be more religious than……men, more involved in……legends that……society……been preserving?"</p><p>“可是在麦曲生，”谢顿说，“女性似乎被当成次等人类。我若假设她们比男性更具宗教倾向，更坚信这个社会所保存的种种传说，这样说正确吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I wouldnt risk my life on……Hari,……Id be willing to risk a weeks income on it."</p><p>“我不会拿我的生命打赌，哈里，不过我愿意押上一周的收入。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Good," said Seldon thoughtfully.</p><p>“很好。”谢顿若有所思地说。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors smiled at him. "Theres a……of your psychohistory, Hari. Rule number 47,854:……downtrodden……more religious than……satisfied."</p><p>铎丝对他微微一笑。“哈里，你的心理史学又多了一点内容。第47854条法则：受压迫者比生活安逸者更容易接受宗教。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon shook……head. "don't joke about psychohistory, Dors.……know Im……looking……tiny rules……for vast generalizations……for means of manipulation. I don't want comparative religiosity as……result of a hundred specific rules. I want something from which I can, after manipulation through some system of mathematicized logic, say, Aha, this group of people will tend to be more religious than that group, provided that……following criteria……met,……that, therefore, when humanity meets with these stimuli, it will react with these responses. "</p><p>谢顿摇了摇头。“铎丝，别拿心理史学开玩笑。你知道我不是在搜集细碎的法则，而是在寻找一般性的通则和操作的方法。我不要一百种特殊法则所导出的比较宗教学。我所要的东西，是藉由某种数学化逻辑系统的运作后，便能让我断言，‘啊哈，只要如下的判准全部符合，这群人就会比那群人更具宗教倾向。因此，当人类遇到这些刺激时，就会表现出这些反应来。’”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"How horrible," said Dors. "You……picturing human beings as simple mechanical devices. Press this button……you will……that twitch."</p><p>“多可怕啊。”铎丝说，“你把人类看成简单的机械装置，只要按下这个按钮，就会得到那种抽动。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"No, because there will be many buttons pushing simultaneously to varying degrees……eliciting so many responses of different sorts that overall……predictions of……future will be statistical in nature, so that……individual human being will remain a free agent."</p><p>“并非如此，因为同时会有许多按钮，被按下的程度则各不相同，引发的反应因而五花八门不计其数。所以说，对未来的整体预测必将是统计性的，而每个人仍然都是自由因子。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"How……you know this?"</p><p>“你怎么知道？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I cant," said Seldon.……least, I don't know……I feel it to be……It is what I consider to be……way things ought to……If I……find……axioms,……fundamental Laws of Humanics, so to speak,……the necessary mathematical treatment, then I will have my psychohistory. I have proved that, in theory, this is possible--"</p><p>“我无法知道。”谢顿说，“至少，我还不知道。我只是有这种感觉，认为事情应该这样才对。如果我能找到一组公设，比如说人性学基本定律，再加上必要的数学运算方法，我就会得到我想要的心理史学。我已经证明过，理论上是可能的……”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"But impractical, right?"</p><p>“但是并不实际？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I keep saying so."</p><p>“我一直都这样说。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>A small smile curved Dorss lips,……that what……are doing, Hari, looking……some sort of solution to this problem?"</p><p>铎丝的嘴角露出一抹微笑。“哈里，这就是你正在做的吗，为这个问题寻找某种解答？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I don't know. I swear to……I don't know.……Chetter Hummin is so anxious to find a solution and,……some reason, I am anxious to please him. He is so persuasive a man."</p><p>“我不知道，我向你发誓我不知道。可是契特·夫铭如此渴望找到一个答案，而且不知道为什么，我也渴望能满足他。他是如此具有说服力。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Yes, I know."</p><p>“是的，我知道。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon……that comment pass, although a small frown flitted across……face. </p><p>谢顿并未深究这句话的意思，脸上却迅速掠过一丝愁容。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon continued. "Hummin insists……Empire is decaying, that it will collapse, that psychohistory is……only hope……saving it--or cushioning it or ameliorating it--and that without it humanity will be destroyed……at……very least, go through prolonged misery. He seems to place……responsibility……preventing that on……Now,……Empire will certainly last my time,……if Im to live at ease, I must lift that responsibility from my shoulders. I must convince myself--and even convince Hummin--that psychohistory is……a practical……out that, despite theory, it cannot be developed. So I must follow up as many leads as I……and show that each……must fail."</p><p>谢顿继续说：“夫铭坚持帝国正在衰败，并说它终将崩溃，又说若想拯救帝国，或是缓冲或改善银河的命运，心理史学将是唯一的希望。他还说倘若没有心理史学，人类终将遭到毁灭，或至少会经历一段长久的悲惨岁月。他似乎把这个重责大任，摆到我一个人身上。虽然在我有生之年，帝国绝对不会崩溃，但我若想活得心安理得，就必须把这个重担卸下来。我必须说服自己……甚至要说服夫铭……心理史学并非实际可行的方法；尽管有理论，却无法真正建立。所以每条可能的途径我都得走走看，才能证明没有任何一条活路。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Leads? Like going back in history to a time when human society……smaller than it is now?"</p><p>“途径？像是回溯到人类社会小于如今的时代？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Much smaller.……far less complex."</p><p>“要小很多，而且简单得多。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"And showing that a solution is still impractical?"</p><p>“然后证明实际上仍然无解。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Yes."</p><p>“没错。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"But……is going to describe……early world……you? If……Mycogenians have some coherent picture of……primordial Galaxy, Sunmaster certainly won't reveal it to a tribesman. No Mycogenian will. This is an ingrown society--how many times have we already said it?--and……members……suspicious of tribesmen to……point of paranoia. Theyll tell us nothing."</p><p>“可是谁来为你描述那个早期世界呢？即使麦曲生人拥有太初银河的完整描述，日主也当然不会透露给一个外族人。没有任何麦曲生人会那么做。这是个故步自封的社会，这句成语我们用过多少次了？而且它的成员对外族人的提防已经到了偏执的地步，他们什么也不会告诉我们的。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I will have to think of a……to persuade some Mycogenians to talk. Those Sisters,……instance."</p><p>“我必须想个办法说服某些麦曲生人开口，比如说那对姐妹。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"They won't even hear you, male that……are,……more than Sunmaster hears……And even if they do talk to you, what would they know……a……catch phrases?"</p><p>“她们甚至不会听到你说的话，因为你是男性，正如日主对我装聋作哑一样。即使她们愿意和你说话，除了几句口号之外，她们还会知道什么呢？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I must start somewhere."</p><p>“我必须从某处着手。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors said, "Well,……me think. Hummin says I must protect……and I interpret that as meaning I must help……when I can. What do I know about religion? Thats nowhere near my specialty,……know. I have always dealt with economic forces, rather than philosophic forces,……you can't split history into neat little nonoverlapping divisions.……instance, religions tend to accumulate wealth when successful……that eventually tends to distort……economic development of a society. There, incidentally, is……of……numerous rules of human history that youll have to derive from your basic Laws of Humanics or whatever……called them. But……"</p><p>铎丝说：“好吧，让我想想。夫铭说过我必须保护你，我把这句话解释为必须尽力帮助你。我对宗教了解多少呢？你可知道，那和我的专长相隔甚远。我研究的一向是各种经济力量，而不是那些哲学性力量，可是，你不能把历史分割成许多毫不相交的小单元。举例而言，成功的宗教具有积聚财富的倾向，到头来就会扭曲一个社会的经济发展。顺便提一下，这是人类历史的无数法则之一，你的人性学基本定律，或者无论你管它叫什么，都必须能把它导出来。不过……”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>And here, Dorss voice faded away as……lapsed into thought. Seldon watched……cautiously……Dorss eyes glazed as though……was looking deep within herself.</p><p>说到这里，铎丝不知不觉陷入沉思，声音因此逐渐消失。谢顿仔细打量她，发现她的双眼呆滞无神，仿佛正在凝视自己内心深处。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Finally……said, "This is……an invariable rule,……it seems to me that on many occasions, a religion……a book--or books--of significance; books that give their ritual, their view of history, their sacred poetry,……who knows what else. Usually, those books……open to……and……a means of proselytization. Sometimes they……secret."</p><p>最后她终于说：“有个并非一成不变的法则，我觉得在许多个案中，一种宗教都拥有一本或数本神圣的典籍，记载着他们的礼仪、他们的历史观、他们的圣诗，谁晓得还有些什么东西。通常这些典籍都对外公开，当做劝人皈依的一种工具。不过有些时候，也可能是不可示人的密典。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Do……think Mycogen……books of that sort?"</p><p>“你认为麦曲生有这种典籍吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"To be truthful," said Dors thoughtfully, "I have never heard of any. I might have if they existed openly--which means they either don't exist or……kept secret. In either case, it seems to me……are……going to……them."</p><p>“说老实话，”铎丝语重心长地说，“我从没听说过。若是公开的典籍，我应该有所耳闻。这就代表它们或是不存在，或是一直被视为密典。不论何者为真，似乎你都见不到。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"At least……a starting point," said Seldon grimly.</p><p>“这至少是个起点。”谢顿绷着脸说。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>The Sisters returned about……hours after Hari……Dors……finished lunch. They were smiling, both of them,……Raindrop Forty-Three,……graver one, held up a gray kirtle……Dorss inspection.</p><p>大约谢顿与铎丝用过午餐两小时后，那对姐妹便再度来访。两人脸上都挂着微笑，较严肃的那位（雨点四十三）拿着一件裰服让铎丝检视。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"It is very attractive," said Dors, smiling widely……nodding……head with a certain sincerity. "I like……clever embroidery here."</p><p>“非常好看。”铎丝露出开怀的笑容，并以一种真诚的态度点着头。“我喜欢这部分的精巧刺绣。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"It is nothing," twittered Raindrop Forty-Five.……is……of my……things……it won't……very well,……you……taller than I……But it will do……a while……we will take……out to……very best kirtlery to……a……that will……you……your tastes perfectly.……will see."</p><p>“没有什么。”雨点四十五以清脆的声音说，“它是我穿旧了的，而且不会非常合身，因为你比我高，但至少能凑合一下。我们会带你到最好的裰服店，买几件完全符合你的身材和品味的。到时你就知道了。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Raindrop Forty-Three, smiling a little nervously……saying nothing……keeping……eyes fixed on……ground, handed a white kirtle to Dors. It……folded neatly. Dors……not attempt to unfold……but passed it on to Seldon. "From……color I should……its yours, Hari."</p><p>雨点四十三露出稍嫌紧张的微笑，不过什么也没说，只是将目光固定在地上，然后把一件白色裰服交给铎丝。那件裰服折叠得很整齐，铎丝并未想要打开，而是直接将它递给谢顿。“哈里，根据颜色判断，我敢说是给你的。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Presumably," said Seldon, "but give it back.……did……give it to me."</p><p>“想必没错。”谢顿说，“但我要你还回去，她并没有直接拿给我。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Oh, Hari," mouthed Dors, shaking……head slightly.</p><p>“喔，哈里。”铎丝做出这几个字的口形，同时微微摇了摇头。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"No," said Seldon firmly. "She……not give it to……Give it back to……and I'll wait……her to give it to me."</p><p>“不行。”谢顿坚决地说，“她并没有直接拿给我。把衣服还给她，我等她自己拿给我。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors hesitated, then made a half-hearted attempt to pass……kirtle back to Raindrop Forty-Three.</p><p>铎丝迟疑了一下，然后勉强试图将那件裰服还给雨点四十三。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>The Sister……her hands behind……back……moved away,……life seeming to drain from……face. Raindrop Forty-Five stole a glance at Seldon, a very quick one, then took a quick step toward Raindrop Forty-Three……put……arms about her.</p><p>那位姐妹却将双手背到背后，身子闪开，脸上的血色似乎完全消失无踪。雨点四十五偷偷瞥了谢顿一眼，动作非常迅速，然后快步走向雨点四十三，张开双臂将她抱住。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors said, "Come, Hari, Im sure that Sisters……not permitted to talk to……who……not related to them. Whats……use of making……miserable?……can't help it."</p><p>铎丝说：“好啦，哈里。我确信姐妹们不准和非亲非故的男性说话。你让她这么为难又有什么用？她根本身不由己。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I don't believe it," said Seldon harshly.……there is such a rule, it applies only to Brothers. I doubt very much that shes ever……a tribesman before."</p><p>“我可不相信。”谢顿粗声道，“如果真有这样一条规定，也只适用于兄弟们。我非常怀疑她以前遇见过任何外族男子。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors said to Raindrop Forty-Three in a soft voice, "Have……ever……a tribesman before, Sister, or a tribeswoman?"</p><p>铎丝以轻柔的声音对雨点四十三说：“姐妹，你遇见过外族男子，或是外族女子吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>A long hesitation……then a slow negative shake of……head.</p><p>犹豫许久之后，她才慢慢摇了摇头。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon threw……his arms. "Well, there……are. If there is a rule of silence, it applies only to……Brothers. Would they have sent these young women--these Sisters--to deal with us if there……any rule against speaking to tribesmen?"</p><p>谢顿摊开双臂。“好，你看吧。即使真有一条保持缄默的规定，它也只适用于兄弟们。若有任何禁止和外族男子说话的规定，他们还会派年轻女子……这两位姐妹……来帮我们吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"It might……Hari, that they were meant to speak only to me……I to you."</p><p>“或许是这样的，哈里，她们只能和我讲话，再由我转达给你。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Nonsense. I don't believe it……I won't believe……I am……merely a tribesman, I am an honored guest in Mycogen, asked to be treated as such by Chetter Hummin……escorted here by Sunmaster Fourteen himself. I will……be treated as though I do……exist. I will be in communication with Sunmaster Fourteen……I will complain bitterly."</p><p>“简直荒谬。我可不信，永远不会相信。我不只是一名外族男子，我还是麦曲生的贵客；契特·夫铭要求他们将我待为上宾，日主十四亲自护送我来到此地。我不要被当成一个不存在的人，我会跟日主十四取得联络，还会向他大吐苦水。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Raindrop Forty-Five began to……and Raindrop Forty-Three, retaining……comparative impassivity, nevertheless flushed faintly. </p><p>雨点四十五开始啜泣，雨点四十三则保持着一贯无动于衷的态度，但脸孔也难免涨红少许。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors made as though to appeal to Seldon once again,……he stopped……with a brief……angry outward thrust of……right……and then stared gloweringly at Raindrop Forty-Three.</p><p>铎丝好像打算再向谢顿说情，他却愤怒地猛然伸出右臂，阻止她做进一步的努力。然后，他皱着眉头凝视着雨点四十三。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>And finally……spoke……did……twitter. Rather,……voice trembled hoarsely, as though……had to force it to sound in……direction of a male being……was doing so against……her instincts……desires. </p><p>最后她终于开口，但不再是清脆嘹亮之声。反之，她的声音颤抖而嘶哑，仿佛她必须用力将声音传到一名男性所在的位置，而这样做完全违背她的本能与意愿。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>You must……complain of……tribesman. That would be unjust.……force me to break……custom of……people. What do……want of me?</p><p>“外族男子，你不可以告我们的状，那是不公平的。你强迫我打破我们族人的习俗，到底想要我做什么？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon smiled disarmingly at once……held……his hand. "The garment……brought……The kirtle."</p><p>谢顿立刻露出敌意尽消的笑容，并伸出一只手。“你带给我的那件衣服，那件裰服。”</p></div>
