<div class='layout'><p>"Wait. don't be angry with……I don't expect to be told state secrets. Come……dear." (The word slipped out.)</p><p>“等一等，别生我的气。我并不指望听到什么国家机密。好啦，亲爱的。”他一不小心说溜了嘴。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>He took……arm as……seemed on……point of hurrying away.……remained in place,……he felt……shudder slightly……he released……in embarrassment. </p><p>正在她似乎要匆忙离去时，他抓住她的手臂，令她留在原处。但他感到她在微微颤抖，遂在一阵尴尬中将手松开。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>He said, "Its just that it seems automated."</p><p>他说：“只不过在我看来，一切都是自动的。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Make what……wish of……seeming. Nevertheless, there is room here……human brains……human judgment. Every Brother……Sister……occasion to work here at some time. Some make a profession of it."</p><p>“随便你爱怎样想都可以。然而，这里仍有需要脑力和判断力的地方。每位兄弟和姐妹，一生中总有一段时间在此工作，有些人还将它当成专业。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>She……speaking more freely……but, to……continuing embarrassment, he noticed……left hand move stealthily toward……right……and gently……the spot where he……touched her, as though he……stung her. </p><p>现在她说话更为自由自在，但他仍旧感到尴尬，因为他注意到，她的左手偷偷移向右臂，轻抚着刚才被他抓过的地方，仿佛那儿曾经被他刺了一下。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>It goes on……kilometers……kilometers,……said, "but if we turn here therell he a portion of……fungal section……can see."</p><p>“它们绵延无数公里，”她说，“不过我们若在这里转弯，你就能看到一片真菌区。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>They moved along. Seldon noted……clean everything was.……glass sparkled.……tiled floor seemed moist, though when he seized a moment to bend……touch……it wasnt.……was it slippery--unless……sandals (with……big……protruding in approved Mycogenian fashion)……nonslip soles. </p><p>他们继续前进，谢顿注意到每样东西都清洁无比，连玻璃也晶莹剔透。瓷砖地板似乎是湿的，等到他趁机弯腰摸了一下，却发觉并非如此。而且地板也不滑，或许是他的凉鞋具有防滑鞋底（根据麦曲生社会的习俗，他将拇趾大大方方伸在外面）。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Raindrop Forty-Three……right in……respect. Here……there a Brother or a Sister worked silently, studying gauges, adjusting controls, sometimes engaged in something as unskI'lled as polishing equipment--always absorbed in whatever they were doing.</p><p>有一件事雨点四十三的确没说错。不时可见兄弟或姐妹在默默工作，例如判读量具、调整控制装置，还有些做着诸如擦拭设备这类毫无技术性的工作……不论做的是什么，每个人都全神贯注。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon……careful……to……what they were doing, since he……not want to cause……Sister humiliation in having to answer that……did……know or anger in……having to remind……there were things he must……know. </p><p>谢顿小心地避免问及他们在做些什么，他不想让这位姐妹因为答不出来而感到羞愧，也不想让她因为必须提醒他别乱打听而发脾气。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>They passed through a lightly swinging door……Seldon suddenly noticed……faintest touch of……odor he remembered. He looked at Raindrop Forty-Three,……she seemed unconscious of it……soon he……became used to……</p><p>他们通过一扇微微摇摆的门，谢顿突然察觉到一丝记忆中的味道。他向雨点四十三望去，但她似乎浑然不觉，而他自己也很快就习惯了。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>The character of……light changed suddenly.……rosiness……gone……the brightness too.……seemed to be in a twilight except where equipment……spotlighted……wherever there……a spotlight there seemed to be a Brother or a Sister. Some wore lighted headbands that gleamed with a pearly glow and, in……middle distance, Seldon could see, here……there, small sparks of light moving erratically.</p><p>光线的特征忽然起了重大变化，蔷薇色调与明亮的感觉通通消失。除了有聚光灯为各项设备照明外，四周似乎都笼罩在昏黄的光芒中。在每个聚光处，好像都有一名兄弟或姐妹，有些还戴着发出珍珠般光辉的头带。而在不远的地方，谢顿可以看到四下都有细小的闪光在做不规则运动。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>As they walked, he cast a quick……on……profile. It……all he could really judge……At……other times, he could……cease being conscious of……bulging bald head,……bare eyes,……colorless face. They drowned……individuality……seemed to make……invisible. Here in profile, however, he could……something. Nose, chin, full lips, regularity, beauty.……dim light somehow smoothed……and softened……great upper desert.</p><p>当两人并肩行走时，他朝她的侧面瞥了一眼，那是他能评价她的唯一依据。在其他任何时候，他总是忘不掉她突出的光头、无眉的双眼，以及一张素净的脸庞。它们掩盖了她的个体性，似乎使她变得隐形。然而从这个轮廓中，他却能看出一些别的：鼻子、下巴、丰唇、匀称、美丽。黯淡的光线好像使那个大沙漠不再那么显眼与刺眼。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>He thought with surprise:……could be very beautiful if……grew……hair……arranged it nicely. </p><p>他惊讶地想到，如果留起头发并好好修剪，她可能就是个大美人。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>And then he thought that……couldnt grow……hair.……would be bald……whole life. </p><p>然后他又想到，她无法长出头发，她这一生注定永远光头。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Why?……did they have to do that to her? Sunmaster said it……so that a Mycogenian would know himself……herself)……a Mycogenian……his……her) life.……was that so important that……curse of hairlessness……to be accepted as a badge or mark of identity?</p><p>为什么呢？他们为什么一定要让她变成这样？日主说，是为了使麦曲生人一辈子记得自己是麦曲生人。这点为何那么重要，以致大家都得接受脱毛的诅咒，作为身份的象征与标记？</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>And then, because he……used to arguing both sides in……mind, he thought: Custom is second nature. Be accustomed to a bald head, sufficiently accustomed,……hair on it would seem monstrous, would evoke nausea. He himself……shaved……face every morning, removing……the facial hair, uncomfortable at……merest stubble,……yet he……not think of……face as bald or as being in……way unnatural. Of course, he could grow……facial hair at……time he wished--but he didnt wish to do so.</p><p>然后，因为他习惯从正反两方面思考问题，于是又想到，习俗是第二天性，如果习惯了光头，到了根深蒂固的地步，那么头发就会显得怪异恐怖，令人感到恶心与厌恶。他自己每天早上都会刮脸，将胡须完全除去，剩下一点点胡根都不舒服。但他并不认为自己的脸是秃的，或是有任何不自然。当然，只要他愿意，随时可以留胡子，但他就是不愿那么做。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>He knew that there were worlds on which……men……not shave; in some, they……not even clip or shape……facial hair……let it grow wild. What would they……if they could……his……bald face,……own hairless chin, cheek,……lips?</p><p>他知道在某些世界上，男人一律不刮脸；甚至有些世界的男人根本不修剪胡须，任由它胡乱生长。如果让他们看到自己光秃的脸庞、没有任何胡须的下巴、双颊与嘴唇，他们又会怎么说呢？</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>……meanwhile, he walked with Raindrop Forty-Three--endlessly, it seemed--and every once in a while……guided……by……elbow……it seemed to……that……had grown accustomed to that,……she……not withdraw……hand hastily. Sometimes it remained……nearly a minute.</p><p>他一面想，一面跟着雨点四十三向前走，这条路似乎没有尽头。每隔一会儿，她就会拉着他的手肘引导他。在他的感觉中，她似乎越来越习惯这样做，因为她并未急忙缩回手去，有时还持续将近一分钟。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>She said, "Here! Come here!"</p><p>她说：“这里！到这里来！”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"What is that?" asked Seldon.</p><p>“那是什么？”谢顿问道。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>They were standing before a small tray fI'lled with little spheres, each about……centimeters in diameter. A Brother……was tending……area……who……just placed……tray where it……looked up in mild inquiry.</p><p>他们站在一个小盘子前面，盘内装满了小型球体，每个球体的直径大约二厘米。有位兄弟在照顾这一区，刚才就是他将盘子放在那里的。此时他抬起头来，带着和气的询问神情。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Raindrop Forty-Three said to Seldon in a……voice, "Ask……a few."</p><p>雨点四十三低声对谢顿说：“向他要一些。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon realized……could……speak to a Brother until spoken to……said uncertainly, "May we have a few, B--brother?"</p><p>谢顿明白她不能主动和一位兄弟说话，除非对方先开口。于是他以迟疑的口气说：“我们能要一些吗，兄……兄弟？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Have a handful, Brother," said……other heartily.</p><p>“兄弟，拿一把吧。”对方热诚地答道。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon plucked……one of……spheres……was on……point of handing it to Raindrop Forty-Three when he noticed that……had accepted……invitation as applying to herself……reached in……two handfuls. </p><p>谢顿抓起一个球体，正准备递给雨点四十三，却发现她已将对方的好意解释为同样适用于她，已经伸手拿了两大把。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>The sphere felt glossy, smooth. Seldon said to Raindrop Forty-Three as they moved away from……vat……from……Brother……was in attendance, "Are these supposed to be eaten?" He lifted……sphere cautiously to……nose.</p><p>这种球体感觉上光滑柔润。等到他们离开那个培养桶以及照料该区的那位兄弟之后，谢顿对雨点四十三说：“这些能吃吗？”他举起那个球体，小心翼翼地凑到鼻端。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"They don't smell,"……said sharply.</p><p>“它们没有味道。”她突然冒出一句。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"What……they?"</p><p>“它们究竟是什么？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Dainties.……dainties.……the outside market theyre flavored in different ways,……here in Mycogen we……them unflavored--the only way." </p><p>“美食，未经加工的美食。销到外界的，会经过各种方式的调味，可是在麦曲生，我们一律吃原味……唯一的吃法。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>She……one in……mouth……said, "I never have enough."</p><p>她放进嘴里一个，然后说：“我怎么也吃不够。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon……his sphere into……mouth……felt it dissolve……disappear rapidly.……mouth,……a moment,……liquid……then it slid, almost of……own accord, down……throat.</p><p>谢顿将手上的球体放入嘴里，感觉它迅速溶化殆尽。一时之间，他嘴里出现一股流动的液体，然后几乎自动滑进他的喉咙。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>He stood……a moment, amazed. It……slightly sweet and,……that matter,……an even fainter bitter aftertaste,……the main sensation eluded him. </p><p>他停了一下脚步，感到相当惊讶。它有一点点甜味，后来甚至出现一丝更淡的苦味，但主要的感觉却令他难以捉摸。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>May I have another? he said.</p><p>“我能再吃一个吗？”他说。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Have half a dozen," said Raindrop Forty-Three, holding……her hand. "They never have quite……same taste twice……have practically no calories. Just taste."</p><p>“再吃五六个吧。”雨点四十三一面说，一面向他伸出手，“它们从来没有重复的口味，而且根本不含热量，只有味道而已。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>She……right. He tried to have……dainty linger in……mouth; he tried licking it carefully; tried biting……a piece. However,……most careful lick destroyed……When a……was crunched……apiece,……rest of it disappeared at once.……each taste……undefinable……not quite like……one before.</p><p>她说得没错。他试图让这种美食在口中多留一会儿；试图小心地舔着；试图咬下一小口。然而，不论他多么小心，它也经不住轻轻的一舔。而只要稍微咬下一点，其余部分也立刻消失。每个球体的味道都无以名状，而且都和先前吃的不尽相同。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"The only trouble is," said……Sister happily, "that every once in a while……have a very unusual……and……never forget……but……never have it again either. I……one when I……nine--"……expression suddenly lost……excitement……she said, "Its a good thing. It teaches……the evanescence of things of……world."</p><p>“唯一的麻烦是，”这位姐妹快活地说，“偶尔你会吃到一个非常特殊的口味，令你终身难忘，可是你却再也碰不到了。我九岁的时候吃过一个……”她的兴奋表情突然敛去，“这是一件好事，让你体认到世事的无常。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>It……a signal, Seldon thought. They……wandered about aimlessly long enough.……had grown used to……and……talking to him.……now……conversation……to come to……point. Now!</p><p>这是个讯号，谢顿心想。他们漫无目标地逛了许久，她已经开始习惯他，而且主动和他说话。现在，他们一定要进入正题。就是现在！</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon said, "I come from a world which lies……in……open, Sister, as……worlds do……Trantor. Rain comes or doesnt come,……rivers trickle or……in flood, temperature is high or low. That means harvests……good or bad. Here, however,……environment is truly controlled. Harvests have no choice……to be good.……fortunate Mycogen is."</p><p>谢顿说：“姐妹，我来自一个露天的世界。其实除了川陀之外，其他世界都是那样。雨水时有时无，河水不是太少就是泛滥，温度不是太高就是太低，这就代表收成有好有坏。然而在此地，环境真正受到控制，收成想不好也不行。麦曲生多么幸运啊。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>He waited. There were different possible answers……his course of action would depend on which answer came.</p><p>他开始等待。她的回答可能会有几种不同的方式，他的行动方针将视她如何回答而定。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>She……speaking quite freely……and seemed to have no inhibitions concerning……masculinity, so this long tour……served……purpose. Raindrop Forty-Three said, "The environment is……that easy to control. There are, occasionally, viral infections……there……sometimes unexpected……undesirable mutations. There……times when whole vast batches wither or……worthless."</p><p>现在她说话已经自由自在，似乎对他这位男性不再有任何心防，所以这趟长途旅程的目的业已达到。雨点四十三说：“环境也不是那么容易控制。偶尔会有病毒感染，有时还会有意料之外的不良突变。还有一些时候，大批作物会整个枯萎或变得毫无价值。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"You astonish……And what happens then?"</p><p>“你这话令我惊讶。那时会怎样处理？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"There is usually no recourse……to destroy……spoiled batches, even those that……merely suspected of spoilage. Trays……tanks must be totally sterilized, sometimes disposed of altogether."</p><p>“通常都没什么办法，只好把腐坏的那批尽数销毁，甚至包括那些仅有腐坏嫌疑的。盘子和水槽一定都要完全消毒，有时还得全部丢弃。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"It amounts to surgery, then," said Seldon. "You……out……diseased tissue."</p><p>“那么，这等于是一种外科手术。”谢顿说，“将染病的组织切除。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Yes."</p><p>“没错。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"And what do……do to prevent such things from happening?"</p><p>“你们如何预防这些情况？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"What……we……We test constantly……any mutations that……spring……any……viruses that……appear,……accidental contamination or alteration of……environment. It rarely happens that we detect anything wrong,……if we……we take drastic action.……result is that……years……very……and even……years affect only fractional bits here……there.……worst year weve ever……fell short of……average by only 12 percent--though that……enough to produce hardship.……trouble is that even……most careful forethought……the most cleverly designed computer programs can't always predict what is essentially unpredictable."</p><p>“我们能怎么办？我们不停地进行测试，看看有没有可能的突变，有没有可能的新病毒，有没有意外的污染或环境的变化。我们很少会侦测到什么问题，但若是发现了，我们就会采取非常措施。这样做的结果，使得歉收的年分非常少，而且纵然歉收，也只是对部分地区稍有影响。历史上收成最差的一年，只比平均年产量少了百分之十二，不过已经足以造成困境。问题是，即使是最谨慎的深谋远虑，以及设计得最高明的电脑程序，也无法百分之百预测本质上不可预测的事物。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>(Seldon felt an involuntary shudder go through him. It……as though……was speaking of psychohistory--but……was only speaking of……microfarm produce of a tiny fraction of humanity, while he himself……considering……the mighty Galactic Empire in every……of……its activities.) </p><p>谢顿觉得一阵颤栗不由自主传遍全身，因为她说的仿佛就是心理史学……事实上，她只是在谈论极少数人所经营的微生农场。而他自己，却是从各个层面在考虑这个庞大的银河帝国。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Unavoidably disheartened, he said, "Surely,……not……unpredictable. There……forces that guide……that care……us all."</p><p>这使他无可避免地感到气馁，他说：“当然，也并非全然不可预测。有些力量在引导、在照顾我们每一个人。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>The Sister stiffened.……turned around toward him, seeming to study……with……penetrating eyes. </p><p>这位姐妹突然僵住。她转头望向谢顿，似乎是以具有透视力的目光在打量他。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>But……she said……"What?"</p><p>但她却只是说：“什么？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon felt uneasy.……seems to me that in speaking of viruses……mutations, were talking about……natural, about phenomena that……subject to natural law. That leaves……of account……supernatural, doesnt……It leaves……that which is……subject to natural……and can, therefore, control natural law."</p><p>谢顿觉得坐立不安。“在我的感觉中，谈到病毒和突变这些话题时，我们只是在讨论自然界的事物、那些服从自然律的各种现象。我们并未考虑到超自然，对不对？并没有包括不受制于自然律，进而能控制自然律的力量。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>She continued to stare at him, as though he……suddenly begun speaking some distant, unknown dialect of Galactic Standard. Again……said, in half a whisper this time, "Wharf."</p><p>她继续盯着他，仿佛他突然改说某种陌生的、不为人知的银河标准语方言。她又说了一句：“什么？”这回音量近乎耳语。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>He continued, stumbling over unfamiliar words that half-embarrassed him. "You must appeal to some great essence, some great spirit, some…… I don't know what to call it."</p><p>他继续结结巴巴地用一些不太熟悉而令自己有几分困窘的词汇说：“你必须求助某种伟大的本体，某种伟大的圣灵，某种……我不知道该叫它什么。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Raindrop Forty-Three said in a voice that rose into higher registers……remained low, "I thought……I thought that……what……meant,……I couldnt believe……Youre accusing us of having religion.……didnt……say……Why didnt……use……word?"</p><p>雨点四十三将音区提高，但仍将音量压低。“我就知道，我就知道你是那个意思，可是我本来不敢相信。你是在指控我们拥有宗教。你为什么不直接那么说？为什么不直接用那个词汇？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>She waited……an answer……Seldon, a little confused at……onslaught, said, "Because thats……a word I use. I call it supernaturalism. "</p><p>她在等待一个答案。谢顿被这轮猛攻弄得有点不知所措，他说：“因为那不是我使用的词汇，我管它叫超自然论。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Call it what……will.……religion……we don't have……Religion is……the tribesmen,……the swarming ho--"</p><p>“随便你怎么称呼。反正它就是宗教，而我们没有这种东西。宗教是外族人才有的，是那群渣……”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>The Sister paused to swallow as though……had come near to choking……Seldon……certain……word……had choked over was--"</p><p>这位姐妹突然住口，吞了一下口水，仿佛差点就要呛死。谢顿可以确定，令她呛到的一定是“渣滓”两个字。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>She……in control again. Speaking slowly……somewhat below……normal soprano,……said,……are……a religious people.……kingdom is of this Galaxy……always……been. If……have a religion--"</p><p>她再度恢复自制，以低于她平常的女高音音调缓缓说道：“我们不是一个信仰宗教的民族，我们的国度是这个银河系，而且一向如此。如果你信教……”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon felt trapped. Somehow he……not counted on this. He raised a hand defensively. "Not really. Im a mathematician……my kingdom is also of this Galaxy.……just that I thought, from……rigidity of your customs, that your kingdom--"</p><p>谢顿感到中了圈套，怎么也没料到会有这种发展。他举起一只手，做出辩护的手势。“不是这样的。我是个数学家，我的国度也是这个银河系。只不过我想到，根据你们那些刻板的习俗，你们的国度……”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"don't think……tribesman. If……customs……rigid, it is because we……mere mI'llions surrounded by bI'llions. Somehow we must mark ourselves……so that we precious……are……lost among your swarms……hordes. We must be marked……by……hairlessness,……clothing,……behavior,……way of life. We must know……we……and we must be sure that……tribesmen know……we are. We labor in……farms so that we……make ourselves valuable in your eyes……thus make certain that……leave us alone. Thats……we……of you…… to leave us alone."</p><p>“外族男子，别那样想。若说我们的习俗刻板，那是因为我们只有几百万人，却被几十亿人包围起来。我们总得设法表现得与众不同，唯有这样，我们这些珍贵的少数，才不会被你们满坑满谷的多数所吞没。我们必须靠我们的脱毛、我们的衣着、我们的行为、我们的生活方式来和他人区隔。我们必须知道自己是什么人，也必须确保你们外族人知道我们是什么人。我们在农场中辛勤工作，好让你们对我们刮目相看，如此才能确保你们放我们一马。这就是我们对你们唯一的要求……放我们一马。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I have no intention of harming……or……of your people. I seek only knowledge, here as everywhere."</p><p>“我无意伤害你或是任何族人。我只是来这里寻求知识，就像在其他地方一样。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"So……insult us by asking about……religion, as though we have ever called on a mysterious, insubstantial spirit to do……us what we cannot do……ourselves."</p><p>“你却借着询问我们的宗教来侮辱我们，仿佛我们曾经仰赖一种神秘的、虚无的圣灵，帮助我们做到我们自己做不到的事。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"There……many people, many worlds……believe in supernaturalism in……form or another…… religion, if……like……word better. We……disagree with them in……way or another,……we……as likely to be wrong in……disbelief as they in their belief. In……case, there is no disgrace in such belief……my questions were……intended as insults."</p><p>“有许多人、许多世界都相信某种形式的超自然论……宗教，你喜欢这样说也可以。我们或许因为某种理由而不同意他们的见解，但我们的不信也有可能是个错误，双方的错误几率刚好一半一半。无论如何，这种信仰没什么可耻的，我的问题也并非打算侮辱任何人。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>But……was……reconciled. "Religion!"……said angrily.……have no need of it."</p><p>她却没有讲和的意思。“宗教！”她气呼呼地说，“我们根本不需要。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldons spirits, having sunk steadily in……course of this exchange, reached bottom. This whole thing, this expedition with Raindrop Forty-Three,……come to nothing.</p><p>在这段对话进行中，谢顿的心持续往下沉，此时则跌到谷底。这整个行动，这趟和雨点四十三所做的远征，最后竟然一无所获。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>But……went on to say,……have something……better. We have history."</p><p>不料她继续说：“我们另有好得多的东西，我们有历史！”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>And Seldons feelings rebounded at once……he smiled.</p><p>谢顿的心情立刻回升，他随即露出笑容。</p></div>

